				\begin{document}$$ \Pr \left(C\kern0.1em \Big|x\right)=\frac{ \Pr (C)\cdot \Pr \left(x\;\Big|C\right)}{ \Pr (x)}, $$\end{document}PrC|x=PrC⋅Prx|CPrx, where C represents G or B. According to Bayesian classification criteria and the assumed equal Pr(C) for transcribed gene region or background non-transcribed region, the class (G or B) with the maximal likelihood Pr(x|C) should also have the maximal posteriori probability and therefore have the maximal probability to be true. The G region is extended by this way, and the λ value for G is also updated recursively.
